{"id": 1762, "date": "2018-04-22T05:00:17", "date_gmt": "2018-04-22T12:00:17", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=1762"}, "modified": "2019-04-13T14:04:23", "modified_gmt": "2019-04-13T21:04:23", "slug": "roll-of-the-dice-until-the-rain-comes", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2018/04/22/roll-of-the-dice-until-the-rain-comes/", "title": {"rendered": "Roll of the Dice: Until the Rain Comes"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>Today&#8217;s entry is an unusual one. I&#8217;ve covered unreleased songs and even work-in-progress snippets, but this is the first essay for which we don&#8217;t even have a scrap of music to listen to.</p>\n<p>The only reason we know that &#8220;Until the Rain Comes&#8221; exists is that its lyrics were included in the 2006 public auction of a notebook containing lyrics from songs Bruce had written in 1968 at the tender age of eighteen.</p>\n<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"1818\" data-permalink=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2018/04/22/roll-of-the-dice-until-the-rain-comes/1968_lyricsnotebook/#main\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/1968_lyricsnotebook.jpg?fit=200%2C291&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"200,291\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"1968_lyricsnotebook\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/1968_lyricsnotebook.jpg?fit=200%2C291&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/1968_lyricsnotebook.jpg?fit=200%2C291&amp;ssl=1\" class=\" wp-image-1818 aligncenter\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/1968_lyricsnotebook.jpg?resize=520%2C757\" alt=\"\" width=\"520\" height=\"757\" /></p>\n<p>The table of contents shows several previously-unknown songs.</p>\n<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"1819\" data-permalink=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2018/04/22/roll-of-the-dice-until-the-rain-comes/1968_lyricsnotebook-contentspage/#main\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/1968_lyricsnotebook-contentspage.jpg?fit=520%2C800&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"520,800\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"1968_lyricsnotebook-contentspage\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/1968_lyricsnotebook-contentspage.jpg?fit=195%2C300&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/1968_lyricsnotebook-contentspage.jpg?fit=520%2C800&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"wp-image-1819 aligncenter\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/1968_lyricsnotebook-contentspage-195x300.jpg?resize=596%2C917\" alt=\"\" width=\"596\" height=\"917\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/1968_lyricsnotebook-contentspage.jpg?resize=195%2C300&amp;ssl=1 195w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/1968_lyricsnotebook-contentspage.jpg?w=520&amp;ssl=1 520w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 596px) 100vw, 596px\" /></p>\n<p>The ninth song, &#8220;Until the Rain Comes,&#8221; is actually known to have been played by Bruce during his solo acoustic shows that spring and summer, but no recording has surfaced.</p>\n<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"1817\" data-permalink=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2018/04/22/roll-of-the-dice-until-the-rain-comes/untiltheraincomes_lyrics/#main\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/untiltheraincomes_lyrics.jpg?fit=640%2C311&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"640,311\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"untiltheraincomes_lyrics\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/untiltheraincomes_lyrics.jpg?fit=300%2C146&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/untiltheraincomes_lyrics.jpg?fit=640%2C311&amp;ssl=1\" class=\" wp-image-1817 aligncenter\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/untiltheraincomes_lyrics-300x146.jpg?resize=664%2C323\" alt=\"\" width=\"664\" height=\"323\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/untiltheraincomes_lyrics.jpg?resize=300%2C146&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/untiltheraincomes_lyrics.jpg?w=640&amp;ssl=1 640w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 664px) 100vw, 664px\" /></p>\n<p>The handwritten lyrics are above (thanks to springsteenlyrics.com), but here they are transcribed:</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><em>Today I sail from the shores of my homeland</em><br />\n<em>reflections upon the water enchant my searching eyes</em><br />\n<em>Across the flaming clouds rides the brave Apollo</em><br />\n<em>until the rain comes leaving silence on the sky</em></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><em>I lay upon the soft green grass and think for many days</em><br />\n<em>voices to my left and right tear me in two ways</em><br />\n<em>Upon reaching the ancient age of 18 I have found</em><br />\n<em>what is round isn&#8217;t round at all, and what is up may be down</em></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><em>A windy day is running near, the white dove flies alone</em><br />\n<em>broken brothers tear the earth and turn into dried up bones</em><br />\n<em>I ask for an answer and do not hear a sound</em><br />\n<em>lies upon lies again, until the rain comes</em></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><em>The emerald waves lap upon the shore</em><br />\n<em>kiss the naked body of the night before</em><br />\n<em>The sweet young sparrow weeps for things she&#8217;s never done</em><br />\n<em>and I&#8217;ll drink her love, when the rain comes</em></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><em>So I cut the ropes that bind my craft to the shore</em><br />\n<em>and sail upon the open sea, where freedom flows so pure</em><br />\n<em>Back upon the sandy beach a child cries with dawn</em><br />\n<em>I&#8217;ll never return again, until the rain comes</em></p>\n<p>Lyrically (and that&#8217;s all we have to go on), &#8220;Until the Rain Comes&#8221; is very much the product of an 18-year-old, newly independent, questioning and unsure, saying goodbye to his childhood and venturing forth into adulthood.</p>\n<p>Perhaps a recording will surface one day and we&#8217;ll hear Bruce breathe life into the song.</p>\n<p><strong>Until the Rain Comes</strong><strong><br />\nNever Recorded</strong><br />\n<strong>First/Last Performed:</strong> mid-1968</p>\n<p>Looking for your favorite Bruce song? Check our <a href=\"http://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/roll-of-the-dice-album-by-album/\">full index</a>. New entries every week!</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>Unearthed handwritten lyrics by an 18-year-old Bruce Springsteen.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 1821, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "default_image_id": 0, "font": "", "enabled": false}, "version": 2}}, "categories": [3], "tags": [1308, 818], "class_list": ["post-1762", "post", "type-post", "status-publish", "format-standard", "has-post-thumbnail", "hentry", "category-roll-of-the-dice", "tag-1968-notebook", "tag-until-the-rain-comes"], "aioseo_notices": [], "jetpack_publicize_connections": [], "jetpack_featured_media_url": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/1968_lyricsnotebook-1.jpg?fit=200%2C291&ssl=1", "jetpack_sharing_enabled": true, "jetpack_shortlink": "https://wp.me/p9w3Lk-sq", "jetpack_likes_enabled": true, "jetpack-related-posts": [{"id": 6806, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2019/01/05/roll-of-